schema.description: [Core] Represents a work assignment that’s been routed to an agent.

Id.title: Agent Work ID
Id.description: Globally unique string that identifies a record.

Name.title: Name
Name.description: An automatically generated ID number that identifies the record.

LastModifiedDate.title: Last Modified Date
LastModifiedDate.description: Date and time when a user last modified this record.

Status.title: Status
Status.description: The working status of the work item. Valid values are: Assigned – The item is assigned to the agent but hasn’t been opened. Canceled – The item no longer needs to be routed. For example: a chat visitor cancels their Omni-Channel routed chat request before it reaches an agent. Closed – The item is closed. Declined – The item was assigned to the agent but the agent explicitly declined it. DeclinedOnPushTimeout – The item was declined because push time-out is enabled and the item request timed out with the agent. Opened – The agent opened the item. Transferred–The item was transferred from an agent to another agent, queue, or skill. Unavailable – The item was assigned to the agent but the agent became unavailable (went offline or lost connection).

CapacityWeight.title: Units of Capacity
CapacityWeight.description: The amount of an agent’s capacity for work items that’s consumed by a work item from this service channel.For example, if cases are assigned a capacity weight of 2, an agent with a capacity of 6 can accept up to 3 cases before the agent is at capacity and can’t receive new work items.

CapacityPercentage.title: Percentage of Capacity
CapacityPercentage.description: The percentage of an agent’s capacity for work items that’s consumed by a specific type of work item from this service channel.When an agent’s combined work items reach 100%, the agent doesn’t receive new work items until there’s enough open capacity for more work. For example, if you give phone calls a capacity percentage of 100, an agent on a call doesn’t receive new work items until the call ends.

RequestDateTime.title: Request Date
RequestDateTime.description: Indicates when the work was requested.

AcceptDateTime.title: Accept Date
AcceptDateTime.description: Indicates when the work item was accepted.

DeclineDateTime.title: Decline Date
DeclineDateTime.description: Date and time when the agent declined this record.

CloseDateTime.title: Close Date
CloseDateTime.description: Indicates when the work item was closed.

SpeedToAnswer.title: Speed To Answer
SpeedToAnswer.description: The amount of time between when the work was requested and when an agent accepted it.

AgentCapacityWhenDeclined.title: Agent Capacity when Declined
AgentCapacityWhenDeclined.description: The agent’s capacity when declining work, either explicitly or through push timeout.

PushTimeout.title: Push Time-Out
PushTimeout.description: The time limit set for an agent to respond to an item before it’s pushed to another agent. The time limit is measured in seconds. This field is available in API version 36.0 and later.

PushTimeoutDateTime.title: Push Time-Out Date
PushTimeoutDateTime.description: The date and time (in UTC) when the push timeout event occurred. This field is available in API version 36.0 and later.

HandleTime.title: Handle Time
HandleTime.description: The amount of time an agent had the work item open. Calculated by CloseDateTime – AcceptedDateTime. If After Conversation Work is in use, HandleTime ends when the AfterConversationActualTime period ends or the agent closes the work item, whichever occurs first.

ActiveTime.title: Active Time
ActiveTime.description: The amount of time an agent actively worked on the work item. Tracks when the item is open and in focus in the agent’s console. If After Conversation Work is in use, ActiveTime ends when the AfterConversationActualTime period ends or the agent closes the work item, whichever occurs first.ActiveTime is tracked only for work that is routed using the tab-based capacity model.

DeclineReason.title: Decline Reason
DeclineReason.description: The provided reason for why an agent declined the work request.

CancelDateTime.title: Cancel Date
CancelDateTime.description: Indicates when the work item was canceled.

ShouldSkipCapacityCheck.title: Should Skip Capacity Check
ShouldSkipCapacityCheck.description: Indicates whether to skip checking an agent’s available capacity (true) or not (false) when an externally routed work item is created. This field is used when agents can simultaneously handle work from both Omni-Channel queues and queues using external routing.

RoutingType.title: Routing Type
RoutingType.description: The type of Omni-Channel routing. Possible values are: QueueBased SkillsBased

RoutingModel.title: Routing Model
RoutingModel.description: Determines how incoming work items are routed to agents assigned to a service channel. Possible values are: ExternalRouting LeastActive MostAvailable

RoutingPriority.title: Routing Priority
RoutingPriority.description: The order in which work items from the queue that are associated with the routing configuration are routed to agents.

AssignedDateTime.title: Assign Date
AssignedDateTime.description: Indicates when the work item was assigned to an agent. This field is a calculated field.

IsPreferredUserRequired.title: Is Preferred User Required
IsPreferredUserRequired.description: Indicates whether a work item stays with the preferred user even when the user isn’t available. The default value is false. This field is available in API version 50.0 and later.

AfterConversationActualTime.title: After Conversation Work Actual Time
AfterConversationActualTime.description: The number of seconds an agent spent on After Conversation Work (ACW) after customer contact ended. This field is available in API version 52.0 and later.

IsInterruptible.title: Is Interruptible
IsInterruptible.description: Indicates whether a work item consumes interruptible or primary capacity. The default value is false. Available in API version 57.0 and later when the Interruptible Capacity feature is enabled.

AcwExtensionCount.title: After Conversation Work Extension Count
AcwExtensionCount.description: The number of times that an agent extended the After Conversation Work (ACW) timer. This field is available in API version 55.0 and later.

AcwExtensionDuration.title: After Conversation Work Extension Duration
AcwExtensionDuration.description: The length of time (in seconds) that the After Conversation Work (ACW) timer was extended each time that the agent extended the timer. This field is available in API version 55.0 and later.To find the total extension duration, multiply this field by AcwExtensionCount or use AfterConversationActualTime.

PausedCapacityWeight.title: Units of Capacity for Paused Work Items

PausedCapacityPercentage.title: Percentage of Capacity for Paused Work Items
